3,http://www.armslist.com/posts/1723003,For Sale:  Stevens (Savage) Model 87D,"Southern Maryland, Maryland, United States",$ 190,"Listed On: Wednesday, August 14, 2013",Rifles,Savage Arms                                                                                ,22 Long Rifle                                                                                ,Semi-automatic                                                                                ,Rifle,"Offered is my Stevens 87D .22 automatic rifle, made by Savage Arms in Excellent Condition. This is one of two of the last of my collection of classic 22 autoloaders from the 50s and 60s when 22s were made of walnut and blue steel. This was known as the Gill Rifle due to the slots on the left side of the receiver in the action area and was sold under many names, this is the 87D model which was the highest grade version. This rifle originally had a factory finish that was a reddish varnish type of finish which I did not care for so I stripped that finish and did my own refinishing job that brought our the natural blonde color and grain of the wood, and it turned out very nice. This rifle can also be made to function as a single shot by moving the bolt handle slightly inwards, a neat feature. The rifle is complete and is missing nothing, it loads, feeds, fires, ejects, and reloads perfectly with the 50 rds of hi veloclity 22 ammo that I put thru in for functions check when I first got it. After those 50 rds, I cleaned it, placed in a silicon gunsock and into my climatically controlled vault where it has sat until I took it out just now to take these pictures. Its a really neat rifle and if you had one as a kid, you know what fun it is. I will meet buyer half way between us geographically for a FTF cash and carry sale in a public place during daylight hours. Buyer must be legal resident of Maryland who is not prohibited by law from owning firearms, active duty Military stationed in Maryland OK. I am not interested in counter offers or trades and I will not ship this rifle. thanks for looking and please email with any questions."
